<br>
Monks Raw AC=1300...Class specific AC:1150<br>
Caster Raw AC:900   Class specific AC:780..<br>
<br>
I would like the raw ac and the real ac to be side by side...So we can see how Good a piece of equipment is for each class. A 30ac Items past a certain point may suck for monks. However an 80AC item past the same point may be worth while...<br>
<br>
Allowing us to SEE the numbers lets us make better Choices with  loot distribution as well as being able to see how our class has imporved...Rather then just masking it behind numbers that are not really acurate..<br>
<br>
When I look at an AC amount I want to know how much I REALLY have....Thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukurk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kurk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 9:44:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2203.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Uh yah.</span><hr size=1> Verant has a lot of nasty little secrets in its code.  Revealing them would probably not be a good idea since I suspect they tweak them more than you would like to know.  If you want to start a riot you could reveal the true damage mitigation and avoidance tables for each class, but the cries for class balancing would never end.  If there were no classes and the game used skill trees instead, then revealing the formulas might make more sense.  Then again, you would probably end up with everyone playing tank mages a la Ultima Online.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umarshalleido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MarshallEido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/02 10:55:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2203.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uh yah.</span><hr size=1> Like how they &quot;tweeked&quot; something and I ended up losing 9 hp's.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http